S</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I don't smoke weed. But I am sitting here drinking a beer. Prolly finish off a 6 pack easy. My husband is smoking a bowl across the room. I don't understand what seperates the two besides the judgement of legal or illegal. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The main difference between the two is simply the fact that you can not tax what can be grown in anyone's backyard.  Yes, I know you can make homemade beer BUT you still need to buy some of the ingredients and thus you pay taxes.<br>
<br>
No way no how will the govt. allow any of us to have that much fun and not get a piece of the action.  <br>
<br>
That being said weed is just like alcohol in that there simply is no problem so long as you moderate your use.  Too much of anything can be bad for you.  I smoke daily, usually later in the evening (after dinner) with the missus.  We either laugh hysterically at sitcoms, look out the front door and watch the hummingbirds at the feeder, and sometimes we just park outside and enjoy the night.<br>
<br>
Today's weed is far different from what I grew up with back in the 70's.  Homegrown was pretty much the bottom of the barrel, now it's the way to go and both quality and quantity have vastly improved what we smoke now vs what we smoked back in the day.<br>
<br>
God bless hydroponics.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aiaka>Aiaka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://209.108.162.247/dancer.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 834<br> <font color=#330000>(7/7/03 8:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=829.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weed should be legalized in the US</span><hr size=1> I won't go into how bad drugs are and how I had to grow up with a brother who was a drug user and all of the things it has done to my family and is still doing to my family because he can not control himself.<br>
